  "prompt": "What is a polite way to address someone in email whose gender you don't know?",
  "response": "When addressing someone in an email whose gender you don't know, you can use the individual's full name or their title and last name. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n1. Use their full name:\n   - Dear [First Name] [Last Name],\n\n2. Use a generic title and last name:\n   - Dear [Dr./Professor/Customer/Manager/Head/Director] [Last Name],\n\nIf you don't have their name or title, you can use a polite and formal greeting:\n   - Dear [Position/Role, e.g., Hiring Committee, Support Team],\n\nIn all instances, maintaining a professional and respectful tone is key.",
